Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the project

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

Changes Made:
=============

1. Package Installation:
   - Installed @vercel/analytics@^2.0.1 using npm
   - Updated package.json with the new dependency
   - Updated package-lock.json with resolved dependencies (147 packages added)

2. Code Integration:
   - Modified: my-website/src/App.jsx
     * Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
     * Added <Analytics /> component at the end of the JSX return statement
     * Component placed after all main UI elements, following React/Vite best practices

Implementation Details:
=======================

Framework: Vite + React
- Used the React-specific Analytics component from '@vercel/analytics/react'
- Placed the Analytics component in App.jsx, the root application component
- Component is rendered inside the main app fragment, ensuring it loads on all pages

The Analytics component will automatically:
- Track page views across all routes (/, /projects, /experiences, /contact)
- Work seamlessly with the custom routing implementation in the app
- Send data to Vercel's analytics dashboard once deployed

